{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove VAT from text-to-speech voices for computer operating systems",
        "additional_details": "Assistive technology software applications designed for people who have visual impairment, dyslexia etc are eligible for UK Disability VAT Exemption, however the text-to-speech voices that such software use are not VAT zero rated or eligible for UK Disability VAT Exemption\r\nWe ask that text-to-speech voices are given the zero rated VAT status, or UK Disability VAT Exemption eligibility as with other reading aids.",
        "background": "Make text-to-speech voices for computer operating systems VAT zero rated, or eligible for UK Disability VAT Exemption.",
